article.description: — Tymu Chenery's 22 points helped Binghamton defeat Stonehill 79-64 on Saturday.
article.headline: Binghamton defeats Stonehill 79-64
article.story: EASTON, Mass. -- — Tymu Chenery's 22 points helped Binghamton defeat Stonehill 79-64 on Saturday. Chenery also added five blocks for the Bearcats (5-4). Nehemiah Benson scored 17 points and added nine rebounds. Chris Walker shot 4 for 11 (3 for 7 from 3-point range) and 3 of 3 from the free throw line to finish with 14 points. Max Zegarowski led the Skyhawks (1-8) in scoring, finishing with 20 points and seven rebounds. Stonehill also got 19 points from Tony Felder. Jackson Benigni also recorded 12 points and two steals. The loss was the Skyhawks' seventh straight. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
